Wash and dry all produce. Halve, core, and thinly slice @Long Green Pepper{1}(halved, cored, and thinly sliced crosswise into strips). Pat @Diced Steak{10%oz} dry with #paper towels{}.

Heat a drizzle of @Vegetable Oil{2%tsp} in a large, preferably #nonstick pan{} over medium-high heat. Add green pepper and cook, stirring occasionally, until slightly softened, ~{3-4%minutes}.

Add steak to pan with green pepper. Season with @Southwest Spice Blend{1%tbsp}, @Pepper{to taste}, and a big pinch of @Salt{to taste}. Cook, stirring occasionally, until green pepper is tender and steak is browned and cooked through, ~{2-3%minutes}. Turn off heat; remove from pan. Wipe out pan.

Place @Flour Tortillas{2} on a clean work surface or #cutting board{}. Sprinkle one half of each tortilla with @Pepper Jack Cheese{1/2%cup}. Top with steak mixture, then sprinkle with @Mexican Cheese Blend{1/2%cup}. Fold tortillas in half to create quesadillas.

Heat a drizzle of oil in pan used for steak over medium heat. Add quesadillas and cook until tortillas are golden brown and cheese has melted, ~{3-4%minutes} per side.

> For 4 SERVINGS: Cook quesadillas in batches.

Slice quesadillas into 3 wedges each; divide between #plates{}. Dollop with @Smoky Red Pepper Crema{4%tbsp} and drizzle with @Hot Sauce{1%tsp} to taste. Serve.